.SH SHPowerDensityLC
Compute the power spectral density of a complex function for a single
spherical harmonic degree.
.SH Usage
\f[CR]psd\f[R] = SHPowerDensityLC (\f[CR]cilm\f[R], \f[CR]l\f[R])
.SH Parameters
.TP
\f[CR]psd\f[R] : output, real(dp)
Power spectral density of the complex function for spherical harmonic
degree \f[CR]l\f[R].
.TP
\f[CR]cilm\f[R] : input, complex(dp), dimension (2, \f[CR]lmaxin\f[R]+1, \f[CR]lmaxin\f[R]+1)
The complex function expressed in complex spherical harmonics.
.TP
\f[CR]l\f[R] : input, integer(int32)
The spherical harmonic degree.
This must be less than or equal to \f[CR]lmaxin\f[R].
.SH Description
\f[CR]SHPowerDensityLC\f[R] will calculate the power spectral density of
a complex function expressed in complex 4\-pi normalized spherical
harmonics for a single spherical harmonic degree \f[CR]l\f[R].
This is calculated as:
.PP
\f[CR]psd = Sum_{i=1}\(ha2 Sum_{m=0}\(hal | cilm(i, l+1, m+1) |**2 / (2l + 1)\f[R].
